to prepare for a call with your advisor Home About Blog Sign in More Use tab to navigate through the menu All Posts Search Aater Suleman Oct 3 min read to prepare for a call with your advisor Advisors play a critical role in the success of This is especially true for ETS firms where the norms of doing business or measuring a business are not common Making the best use of the face time with advisors is We covered this topic in our blog series on However, we want to deep dive further into one of the areas discussed in that blog – the Preparation is the key to maximizing the value of face time with your As a rule of thumb, an hour meeting requires at least an hour of preparation to be very Two hours of preparation is even Following are some very tactical steps to do in your preparation: Make sure you are using your standard template, if you do not have a standard template you should have Keep the slide templates consistent as it reduces the time it takes for the advisors to consume the Gather the latest data and present it in the standard Highlight the parts you want to highlight either on a new slide or using an Do you change the format just to draw attention to certain parts? An entire blog can be written just on the topic of what data shall be included but we have provided a list as an attachment to this Click here and request permission to see a very simple template we have used in our past Follow the same agenda as last time, only change the parts that are necessary to This builds a rhythm for the meetings that allow you to have continuous improvement, rather than every meeting being a Include in your presentation a recap of the last This can simply be a list of discussions from last time and where have you landed on each of the items and if you need any further This shows the advisors that there is continuity of thought and that you are consuming the advice they are giving Advisors need to stay motivated to give you their Review the last meeting’s minutes to ensure you are adding to the agenda any items that were deferred to this This shows your preparation and completeness to the Advisors like to spend more time with founders where they see their time is not Review the commitments and be ready to share your progress (and ask for progress from the advisor). This is a level You need to show accountability and hold the advisor Because you are the biggest Make a list of your current problems, and categorize them into issues you know how to Issues you have an idea on how to solve, but can use And issues you do not know how to solve and need to From here, it is best to pick one or two and highlight them clearly as the main discussions you would like to have in the Provide ample context – or the items you want to go deep into it is best to have some data, visuals, or a concise description created to show why this decision issue is Nothing is more frustrating to the advisor than when a founder poses a large open ended question with no They have to keep poking at the founder like working with a vending machine to Either they give up and provide generic, often inapplicable advice or they spend most of the time learning with no time left for actual brainstorming of the Remember to show that you have done your homework – what work have you done, what options you have considered (where applicable) and what help have you Advisors will be able to quickly guide you and move you forward if they know what you have already done, otherwise time gets wasted in them telling you things you have already done and before you get to next steps, it becomes time to move to the next This also shows that you are respecting the time of the Reserved for future Do you have any ideas? Please share them with us here or on You can access our proposed template for such a meeting here . Volunteer Search Search Close this search Practice Without Pressure Practice Without Pressure Practice Without Pressure (PWP) is a program developed to work with individuals with intellectual and physical disabilities who are unable to obtain medical, dental, or personal care services due to fear of the procedure, the use of sedation anesthesia, or because of Providing these services without the use of restraint or sedation will result in less risk for the Member and more savings for the health Through specialized training and creating a supportive atmosphere, PWP aims to eliminate the need for sedation, anesthesia, and restraint in providing medical, dental, or personal care services to individuals with If successful after testing the model, this is a possible benefit to be included in Medicaid state plans or waiver benefits to recoup the costs of the Changing Medical Care Along with the goal of eliminating restraint practices in medical, dental, and personal care procedures, the PWP model also aims to make these changes to the healthcare experience that individuals with disabilities often run Here is a list of changes we want to see in medical Less daily stress for patients, caregivers, and healthcare professionals Decrease appointment time Overall savings in cost Decreased usage of emergency room visits, especially for oral health issues Adding PWP as a Medicaid payable benefit in the Why Morgan s MAC? With PWP partnering at Morgan’s MAC, it allows the program to directly tie into Drivers of Health (NMDOH). Both entities will work together to increase the ability of primary care and behavioral health professionals to provide more care to patients who need Since the program includes both caregivers and professionals, both MACers and MAC members will History Deborah Jastrebski, a mother of three, created PWP for her oldest, Marc, who has Down syndrome and significant heart Marc became frightened of anything medical dental, even haircuts, in his personal This fear caused procedures to be very difficult for him, as well as his mother and the professionals that provided Providers often used restraint and sedation as methods to complete the Unfortunately, this only led to more trauma and continued the cycle of Jastrebski knew there was a better She not only wanted to better her son’s experience but also to help others within the disability By she had created the PWP from scratch and over time it has become the respected and nationally known entity that it is We are more than just a theme park! We also have less farmable soil than ever We only have years of farmable soil So, if we can t increase our food production using conventional agriculture, we need to do it hydroponically and in our own ​ The average American spends $751 on fruits and vegetables every year, most of which gets thrown away before it s By growing your own produce and only harvesting what you want to eat when you want to eat it, you re saving money and decreasing food ​ When you re using a Fable Refrigerator, you re eating more nutritious food as well as minimizing your impact on the Produce usually travels over miles by plane, truck, and car before it reaches your table— a process that can take up to fifteen Not only does this create a lot carbon emissions, but produce is severly , even after it is or cryogenically Produce is most nutritious only for the first hours after The Fable Refrigerator gives you immediate access to fruits and And, because your food doesn t have to travel thousands of miles to reach your table, you re also reducing your carbon ​ Our Future It doesn’t have to stop at a farm in your The future of Fable is a new line of appliances that normalize growing food at home and The Fable Evergarden is a appliance dedicated solely to the production of It s counterpart, the Fable Sprout is a smaller, more accessible version that can be housed in an office space, college dorm, or a cramped Imagine if we could use Fable to reach into food deserts and provide food insecure families a way to have nutrient rich meals at their ​ The future of farming is hydroponic, and it s in your Want to get involved? Feeling anxious at times is perfectly You’re bound to feel nervous before an important work presentation or your child’s first day at What’s not normal is to feel anxious most or all of the If anxiety rules your life, it’s become a mental health The most common kind is a generalized anxiety disorder, where everything from visiting the grocery store to making decisions is a source of stress and Some people have anxiety that focuses on a specific situation or These are phobias — fear of flying, heights, and spiders are common Social anxiety disorder is a phobia that centers on a fear of being in social Anxiety disorders are distressing and often However, with expert treatment at Breakthru Psychiatric Solutions, you can overcome abnormal What symptoms do anxiety disorders cause? Anxiety disorders cause both psychological and physical Common symptoms include: Nervousness Muscle tension Restlessness Difficulties concentrating Rapid heart rate Fast, shallow breathing Excessive sweating Trembling Chronic fatigue Disrupted sleep Panic attacks Panic attacks are frightening experiences where your anxiety grows so severe that you can’t function In addition to sweating, shaking, and a pounding heart, you might have chest pain and difficulty catching your Panic attacks can leave you unable to speak or move, or you might cry or scream Further, panic attacks are such horrible experiences that you’re likely to adopt avoidance That means isolating yourself to where you feel safest, so you reduce the risk of further Many people develop depression along with anxiety, adding to the severe effects you can experience if these disorders go How are anxiety disorders treated? When you seek help for anxiety at Breakthru Psychiatric Solutions, Giles performs a comprehensive psychiatric This process enables her to understand your condition and how it’s affecting There are several effective treatments for anxiety, including: Psychotherapy Psychotherapy takes many forms, all of which involve talking about your You might benefit from interpersonal psychotherapy, which helps you process experiences and problems that could be triggering your anxiety and Cognitive behavioral therapy is also helpful for anxiety, showing you how to manage your fears Giles may recommend a therapist in the community to Medication medication can help reduce the severity of your Antidepressants are the first line treatment for treating anxiety in addition to These medications might also help, if you also have Transcranial magnetic stimulation (TMS) TMS is a noninvasive therapy that uses magnets to target specific areas of your brain linked to It helps adjust and calm the brain’s neuronal communications to combat the effects of anxiety and Ketamine Giles offers IV (intravenous) ketamine therapy and intranasal esketamine (Spravato® nasal spray). Ketamine can have rapid and dramatic effects on depression and TMS and ketamine are innovative approaches to treating anxiety and aren’t as widely available as other Many patients find that their symptoms improve To find the treatment combination that’s right for you, call Breakthru Psychiatric Solutions today or request an a
